OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780582265
OL,3,C'It'll change everything': Poverty-
OL,4,Cstricken Haiti yearns for World Cup
OL,5,Cglory
OL,7,FThe Haitian national side has made it
OL,8,Fthrough to the finals of the Fifa
OL,9,FWorld Cup for the first time since
OL,10,F1974, carrying the hopes of a nation,
OL,11,Fwhich for decades has had so little
OL,12,Freason for optimism.
OL,14,FThose who play barefoot in the city's
OL,15,Frough open spaces are craving a
OL,16,Fdistraction from the grinding gang
OL,17,Fviolence of their home, yet they have
OL,18,Fno chance of ever seeing a match.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780582265
OL,3,C'It'll change everything': Poverty-
OL,4,Cstricken Haiti yearns for World Cup
OL,5,Cglory
OL,7,FNot only are the costs prohibitive for
OL,8,Fthe poorest country to qualify, but
OL,9,FHaiti is also one of the few competing
OL,10,Fcountries facing a travel ban for the
OL,11,Ftournament, along with Iran, Senegal,
OL,12,Fand the Ivory Coast.
OL,14,FLast night Haiti made a powerful
OL,15,Fstatement of intent with a four nil
OL,16,Fdrubbing of New Zealand in a friendly
OL,17,Fin Fort Lauderdale.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780582265
OL,3,C'It'll change everything': Poverty-
OL,4,Cstricken Haiti yearns for World Cup
OL,5,Cglory
OL,7,FThe electric atmosphere charged by
OL,8,Fthousands of the Haitian diaspora
OL,9,Fwho'd come to watch their side. Many
OL,10,Fwon't be able to afford tickets to the
OL,11,FWorld Cup games, and those in Haiti
OL,12,Fhave no chance of going.
OL,14,FFrantz Babyson, 16, whose house in
OL,15,FPort-au-Prince was burned down by
OL,16,Fgangs, says despite all that, he can't
OL,17,Fwait for the matches to begin.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780582265
OL,3,C'It'll change everything': Poverty-
OL,4,Cstricken Haiti yearns for World Cup
OL,5,Cglory
OL,7,F"Haiti must become Champions, so that
OL,8,Fthe country doesn't have any more
OL,9,Fdifficulties," he said. He, like every
OL,10,Fother fan here, has no choice but to
OL,11,Fwatch on TV.
OL,13,FAnother 16-year-old, Robinson Castin,
OL,14,Fwho has also been displaced by
OL,15,Fviolence, says he hopes the players
OL,16,Fhave a good World Cup so that Haiti
OL,17,Fcan advance further.
OL,19,F"I hear people saying that if Haiti
OL,20,Fbecomes the Champion, it will change
OL,21,Feverything".
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@NO]{D@AOU}D@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
